==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perfuse
<hw>Per*fuse"</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*f⟦umac⟧z")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Perfused</conjf>
<pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*f⟦umac⟧zd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Perfusing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>perfusus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>perfundere</ets> to pour over; <ets>per + fundere</ets> to
pour.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To suffuse; to fill full or to
excess.</def> <rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pass a liquid through or over; <as>as, the
isolated kidney was <ex>perfused</ex> with saline
solution</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Surgery)</fld> <def>To pass (a liquid) through an
organ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perfusion</ent>⟦br⟧
